Kind of funny to give this place 4 stars.  I tried 3 different things and didn't really like any of them.  BUT, I loved the menu.  I love restaurants that shy away from the traditional and they had a lot of interesting stuff on the menu.  I'm hoping some of them I would have liked (not sure if I'll give them another try).I had a scallop/tuna roll (not sure of the names of any of this stuff) that was pretty light on the scallop.  A beef/eel dish that turned out to be basically meatballs with a teriyaki sauce and an ebi/shrimp fried in noodles.  The ebi was cold and raw in the middle, I told the waiter (not sure if he understood me) and he eventually said that was normal.  Not sure if it was but it took me by surprise.
